		 data-has-pos="true" 
		 data-additional=";weathertoday=lightrain;weathertomorrow=lightshowers" 
		 data-nav="news,world"
		 data-pgid="13847208" 
		 data-trigger-once="gpt:ready"></div>
			<script type="text/javascript" src="/assets/script/modules/async_gpt.js?v=69"></script>
	<p>None from Bangladeshi enclaves within India opted for Bangladesh, while 979 people from Indian enclaves living inside Bangladesh applied for Indian citizenship, said Akhteruzzman Azad, the chief government administrator for Bangladeshs Kurigram district. The shifting of the people to the Indian side will be completed by November this year. Several television news channels in both countries broadcast the celebrations live. </p><p>This will end nearly seven decades of deprivation the people living in the enclaves have had to suffer being virtually owned by no one, said the Bangladeshi English language <em>Daily Star </em>newspaper. </p>		
		<span id="article__content-bottom"></span>			     
		
		
